			"title": "DG-33",
			"description": "Task: Replace the current static horse art with a 4-frame animated horse presentation in the run scene.\n\nThe run scene currently uses one static horse texture for both horses in the carriage team. The horse art now needs a simple 4-frame running or pulling loop so the team reads as alive and in motion during normal gameplay. This should match the existing topdown north-facing view and remain appropriate for horses pulling the carriage, not a loose free-running animal. Keep the current horse placement, harness alignment, collision footprint, gameplay behavior, and wagon handling unchanged.\n\nUse the animated horse sheet in the current wagon rig so both horses visibly animate during a run instead of appearing static. Keep the implementation focused on the horse presentation only unless a small supporting scene or script change is required to make the animation play correctly. The two horse sprites should continue to work with the existing wagon visual effects, restart flow, and return-to-title flow.\n\nAffected files:\n- Assets/Tilesets/Horse/*\n- Scenes/RunScene/RunScene.tscn\n- Scenes/RunScene/run_scene.gd\n- Tests/Unit/test_run_scene.gd\n\nDone when: by launching the game and playing a run, both horses visibly play the new 4-frame animation instead of remaining static, their placement still matches the existing carriage rig and harness setup, restart and return flows do not break the animation, and the rest of the run presentation still behaves normally.",
