			"title": "DG-34",
			"description": "Task: Replace the current static jackalope hazard art with the new 48x32 animated jackalope sheet.\n\nThe run scene currently uses one static jackalope texture for the livestock crossing hazard. The new jackalope art now uses a wider 48x32 animated sheet so the crossing hazard can read as a fast bounding animal instead of a still image sliding across the road. This is an art-integration ticket, not a hazard-design rewrite. Keep the current hazard role, crossing behavior, spawn timing, damage, collision expectations, and run balance unchanged unless a small size or placement adjustment is required to keep the new art aligned with the existing gameplay.\n\nUse the new animated 48x32 jackalope sheet in the hazard presentation so the jackalope visibly animates during normal crossing behavior. Because the new art is wider than the old 32x32 sheet, update the visual presentation and any supporting size or placement wiring needed so the animated hazard still enters, crosses, and reads correctly at gameplay scale. Keep the implementation scoped to the jackalope hazard presentation only unless a small supporting scene or script update is required to make that animation play correctly.\n\nAffected files:\n- Assets/Tilesets/Hazards/Jackalope/*\n- Scripts/Hazards/hazard_spawner.gd\n- Scenes/RunScene/RunScene.tscn\n- Scenes/RunScene/run_scene.gd\n- Tests/Unit/test_hazard_spawner.gd\n- Tests/Unit/test_run_scene.gd\n\nDone when: by launching the game and playing normal runs, jackalope hazards visibly animate with the new 48x32 sheet during their crossing behavior, their on-road placement still matches the existing hazard lane reads, collisions and crossings still behave normally, and the wider art does not introduce obvious visual or gameplay breakage.",
