			"title": "DG-35",
			"description": "Task: Pull the horse team closer to the wagon in the run scene.\n\nIn the current topdown carriage rig, the horses sit too far ahead of the wagon and the team reads visually disconnected in motion. The harness gap looks longer than it should, which makes the carriage and horse team feel less like one unit. Tighten that spacing by moving the horses closer to the wagon, using roughly 16 px as the starting adjustment unless a slightly smaller or larger final value looks better in the live game view.\n\nKeep this as a presentation and layout adjustment only. Do not change the gameplay collision footprint, steering behavior, hazard balance, or run pacing. Update the current wagon rig so the horses, carriage, and harness still line up cleanly after the spacing change and continue to look correct during normal driving, failure presentation, restart, and return flows.\n\nAffected files:\n- Scenes/RunScene/RunScene.tscn\n- Scenes/RunScene/run_scene.gd\n- Tests/Unit/test_run_scene.gd\n\nDone when: by launching the game and playing a normal run, the horses sit visibly closer to the wagon than before, the team reads as one connected carriage rig, the harness still lines up cleanly, and the spacing change does not introduce obvious overlap or presentation breakage during normal play.",
